message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Senegal in the past 100 years is the country's independence from France. On April 4, 1960, Senegal gained its independence, becoming the first country in West Africa to break free from colonial rule. This event marked a significant milestone in Senegal's history and paved the way for the decolonization of other African nations. It led to the establishment of a sovereign Senegalese state and the beginning of a new era of self-governance and national identity.
